Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Slice @mixed olives{1%ounce} crosswise. Slice @Persian cucumbers{2} into thin rounds. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%box}.

On a #baking sheet{}, toss chickpeas, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bake in oven until crisp, about ~{20%minutes}. Set aside and let cool for a few minutes after removing from oven.

> Chickpeas may pop in oven—it's natural.

Heat @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a #small pan{} over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until it just begins to brown, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat. Using a #slotted spoon{}, remove garlic from pan and discard.

Sprinkle @pita bread{2} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @za'atar spice{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place on another baking sheet and toast in oven until crisp and toasty, ~{6-8%minutes}. Remove from oven and let cool. Once cool enough to handle, cut into 1-inch squares. Place squares and cooled chickpeas in a large #bowl{}.

> You can add the pitas to the baking sheet with the chickpeas, if there's room.

Whisk @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon} into pan with garlic oil. Season with salt and pepper.

Add cucumber, olives, tomatoes, parsley, and as much shallot as you like to bowl with pitas and chickpeas. Drizzle with vinaigrette (to taste) and toss thoroughly to coat. Season generously with salt and pepper. Divide between bowls, then sprinkle with @feta cheese{1/2%cup}.